Batch fecundity. Batch fecundity (BF) is the number of eggs each fish releases during a single spawning phase (
Goncalves et al. 2009
). The oocytes from (stages III and IV) were used to determine the batch fecundity of mature females (BF). The ovary was divided into three sub-samples, taken from the front, center, and back and weighed to the nearest 0.1 g. Oocytes ( N O = 67) were separated from the connective tissue and observed under a dissecting microscope (OLYMPUS SZ51) to calculate. Then, BF is estimated by the following ( Fry et al. 2009 )

